Package: NilpotentMinimum
Type: Package
Title: Basic R Functionality for Nilpotent Minimum t-norm fuzzy logic
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Igor", "Yegin",
      email = "igor.yegin@stir.ac.uk",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: Nilpotent Minimum (commonly shortened to NM) is a class of t-norms 
introduced by Fodor (1991). It is an archetypical example of a non-continuous 
t-norm which has a well-defined residuum and a symmetric induced negation with a 
unique fixpoint. This package provides a number of R functions for NM logic 
whose syntax is mostly identical to that of lfl package.
